This is a Hakyll-based wiki. It was originally for my PhD research and used the [[researchr]] tools [[http://reganmian.net/wiki/researchr:start|created by Stian Håklev]].

## Hakyll

Hakyll is a static site generator written in Haskell. I use the following modifications:

**Edit pages with one click** (DONE): Rather than in-browser editing, I'm opting for a link to open the file in MacVim using the `mvim://` protocol. The downside is having an edit link on my published page, but perhaps I can with multiple versions.

**Internal links**: I want to support the wiki link with `[[pagename]]`.

## Style

**Writing**: Prefer clear declarative sentences. These may represent facts or beliefs that can change over time (inspired by [[http://wayoftheduck.com/codex-vitae|Codex Vitae]]). Use claims that can be backed by a link or novel argument. More outlandish claims are still encouraged and can be indicated with "conjecture", "hypothesis", or "prediction".

Example: "Few high achievers support our education system" -> "[[http://blog.ampli.com/2012/03/albert-einstein-quotes-education-15-of.html|Albert Einstein]] and [[http://quotations.about.com/od/marktwainquotes/a/twainedu.htm|Mark Twain]] are examples of high achievers who were displeased with their experience with education." Or "Conjecture: intellectual achievement is inversely correlated with support for the standard education system."

**Page titling**: Prefer Wikipedia's canonical title except for special pages that fall under a namespace.

**HTML style**: Inspired by Smallest Federated Wiki, I use narrow columns, prefer paragraphs over list, restrict headers to h1 and h2 (using htag plugin), and disable Table of Contents.

