## Citations

Using citations increases the authority of claims.

Using linked citations allows readers to read further on a topic.

Researchr uses the **citekey** format [author][year][first-word] as in haklev2014citing to automatically link to a reference page (located at ref:citekey). [[http://www.papersapp.com/mac/|Papers]] has a similar notion of citekey, which allows you to insert the key anywhere by lookup.

The ideal solution would allow you to insert the key anywhere by typing or lookup. In certain contexts such as a wiki or blog, the citekey will generate a URL that links to the author's personal content about that citation as well as a link to the original source (website or PDF).

Stian Haklev and I explored creating a central repository for citekey->wiki mappings. My conclusion is that few if any researchers would enter this information manually, and that there is no way to do it automatically for a critical mass of researchers.

